        'A compass works because Earth has a magnetic field; the magnetised needle in a compass aligns with this field and consistently points towards magnetic north.',
        'The compass reached Europe via Arab traders in the 12th century and revolutionised navigation, allowing sailors to cross open oceans for the first time without sight of land.',
        'Without the compass, the great voyages of exploration — Columbus discovering America, Magellan circumnavigating the globe — would likely never have happened.',
