        'Soft contact lenses — comfortable enough for everyday use — were developed by Czech chemist Otto Wichterle in 1959; they transformed the experience from painful to pleasant.',
        'Today about 140 million people worldwide wear contact lenses; most modern lenses are made from silicone hydrogel, a material that allows oxygen to pass through to the eye.',
        'Disposable daily contact lenses were introduced in 1988, eliminating the need for cleaning solutions and significantly reducing the risk of eye infections.',
