        'Tomlinson sent the email to himself as a test; he later said the first message was probably something like "QWERTYUIOP" — the top row of keyboard letters — just to see if it worked.',
        'Email replaced physical letters and faxes as the primary method of business communication in the 1990s, drastically reducing costs and the time needed to exchange information.',
        'About 347 billion emails are sent every day in 2024 — but roughly 85% of all email is spam, which is why spam filters are one of the most important pieces of software in existence.',
